<p>I have a string in a format similar to <code>1005-abcd</code> and I want to replace the numeric part of this string by another number and make it like <code>1008-abcd</code>. I can achieve this by using the following - </p>  <pre><code>string map {1005 1008} "1005-abcd" </code></pre>  <p>But I have these numbers in form of variables. For example, <code>$source</code> is <code>1005</code> and <code>$new</code> is <code>1008</code>. When I use the same command like this - </p>  <pre><code>string map {$source $new} "1005-abcd" </code></pre>